<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n53092v"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n53" href="#n53092v">N53 (VI.B.46)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n53all.htm#n53092v"> 92(v)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ~ Diar ~</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Three brothers with their followers were chosen: the eldest Rurik ... settled in Novgorod, the second in Bieloozero, the third in Truvor in Izborsk. Three years later two of the brothers died and Rurik took control of the whole of the settlements, dividing the land among his men. In the same year two of Rurik&apos;s followers, Askold ... and <mark>Dir</mark> ... setting out for Constantinople, halted at Kiev and there founded a kingdom, which in 882 was conquered by Rurik&apos;s successor Oleg (O.N. Helgi) and, as the mother of all Russian cities, became the capital of the Russian kingdom. <small> Allen Mawer, <a name="AMTV2" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#AMTV2"><cite title="source">The Vikings</cite></a>, (1913) 74</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
